<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2016-01-31</DATELINE><TITLE>Fatal case of acute gastroenteritis with multiple viral coinfections</TITLE><BODY>Abstract We report a fatal case of acute gastroenteritis in a child with autism spectrum disorder. Multiple viral coinfections were detected by PCR in the patientâ€™s stool and digestive biopsy specimens. As viral detection is not necessarily associated with symptomatic disease, a semi-quantitative approach using cycle treshold values was proposed for the clinical interpretation of PCR. We discuss whether concomitant viral infections could be a risk factor for severe outcome in gastroenteritis cases. Individual risk factors are also addressed.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>